  "content": "\">&rarr;</div>\n          <div style=\"background: rgba(16,185,129,0.2); border: 1px solid var(--accent-green); border-radius: 8px; padding: 10px 16px; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; margin-top: -12px;\">Search</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"flex: 1; min-width: 0;\">\n      <div class=\"mock-label\" style=\"color: var(--accent-green);\">&#9989; Properly aligned</div>\n      <div style=\"background: var(--bg-card); border: 2px solid var(--accent-green); border-radius: 16px; padding: 28px; height: 180px;\">\n        <div style=\"display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 12px; margin-top: 20px;\">\n          <div style=\"background: rgba(59,130,246,0.2); border: 1px solid var(--accent-blue); border-radius: 8px; padding: 10px 16px; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600;\">Input</div>\n          <div style=\"color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 24px;\">&rarr;</div>\n          <div style=\"background: rgba(139,92,246,0.2); border: 1px solid var(--accent-purple); border-radius: 8px; padding: 10px 16px; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600;\">Embed</div>\n          <div style=\"color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 24px;\">&rarr;</div>\n          <div style=\"background: rgba(16,185,129,0.2); border: 1px solid var(--accent-green); border-radius: 8px; padding: 10px 16px; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600;\">Search</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"insight-box\">\n    <p>Every one of these issues is <strong>invisible in the code</strong>.<br>\n    Valid CSS. Semantic HTML. It just doesn't <em>look</em> right.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">03 / 08</div>\n</div>",
